{{Infobox artwork | image_file = The Great Warrior of Montauban - Washington, D.C..jpg | painting_alignment = Front | image_size = 200px | title = The Great Warrior of Montauban | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = Antoine Bourdelle | year = 1898-1900 | type = [[Bronze]] | height_metric = 186.1 | width_metric = 157.5 | length_metric = 61.3 | height_imperial = {{frac|73|1|4}} | width_imperial = 62 | length_imperial = {{frac|24|1|8}} | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = in | city = | museum = | coordinates = | owner = }}
'''''The Great Warrior of Montauban''''' is a bronze sculpture by [[Antoine Bourdelle]].<ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!373053~!0#focus "The Great Warrior of Montauban, (sculpture)"]. ''SIRIS''</ref>
It was commissioned in 1897, by the village of [[Montauban]] to commemorate the [[Franco-Prussian War]].<ref>''A Garden for Art'', Valerie J Fletcher, p. 14.</ref> It was modeled in 1898 to 1900, and cast in 1956.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.flickriver.com/photos/wallyg/3624730605/ |title=Washington DC - Hirshorn Museum and Sculpture Garden - The Great Warrior of Montauban by Emile-Antoine Bourdelle - a photo on Flickriver |publisher=Flickriver.com |date=2009-06-06 |accessdate=2014-08-22}}</ref>
It is an edition of ten; number three is at the [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hirshhorn.si.edu/visit/collection_object.asp?key=32&subkey=4248 |title=Collection Search - Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden &#124; Smithsonian |publisher=Hirshhorn.si.edu |date=2010-12-07 |accessdate=2014-08-22}}</ref> It appeared in ''[[LIFE magazine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.life.com/gallery/40702/image/ugc1088751/seeing-shadows#index/10 |title=LIFE Photos &#124; Classic Pictures From LIFE Magazine's Archives |publisher=LIFE.com |date= |accessdate=2014-08-22}}</ref>
